               <p>JAMES SPARSHOT. I <rs id="t18170219-106-viclabel584" type="occupation">keep a Chandler's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170219-106-victim859 t18170219-106-viclabel584"></join> on <placeName id="t18170219-106-crimeloc585">Saffron-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170219-106-crimeloc585" type="placeName" value="Saffron-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170219-106-crimeloc585" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170219-106-off582 t18170219-106-crimeloc585"></join>. On the 10th of February, I left my hat in my shop; I missed it.</p>
               <p>RACHAEL BARNET. I live in Field-lane. On the 10th of February the prisoner came into my shop, to sell a hat for eighteen pence; he said it was his father's who kept a stall in Fleet-market; I told him to send his father and I would pay him for it; I sent my little girl with him, with the money; he then said, he got the bat in Spa-fields. The next day the prosecutor claimed the hat.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170219-106-verdict586" type="verdictDescription">
